<TITLE> BDR seeks death penalty in draft act </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Dec 15 (bdnews24.com)  Bangladesh Rifles has submitted the draft of Border Guard Bangladesh Act to the law ministry keeping the provision of death sentence as the highest penalty for crimes, including mutiny. BDR director general Maj Gen Moinul Islam on Tuesday met the law minister and state minister for law and handed over the draft to them. State minister for law Quamrul Islam said: "The ministry will give its opinion after examining various aspects of the act." He said according to the present BDR Act, the highest penalty for the internal crimes, including mutiny, is seven years of imprisonment. But the BDR authorities are not satisfied with the degree of punishment and has proposed for raising the penalty in the new act, Islam said. The BDR chief did not talk with the media. bd
